It is in man's nature to conduct war, and I see no more greater future war than between India and China. The enemy of my enemy is my friend, and India and the United States have an enemy in China. True, that the US was not friendly to India for the last 50 years. But, that was based on cold war politics, not on the current political situation.<br>
The United States and China have an alliance that is based on an economic foundation. However, once China's new middle and upper class emerge, they will have no need for American consumers, and a shaky alliance will falter. Who will the US turn to when it is threatened by China? Who else but India. Will India help out? Well, I'm not sure. Alot has to do with how American foreign policies act out and affect asian nations in the years when America can still throw it's weight around and not fear retribution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bindiachinaboard.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pukibaiter>Pukibaiter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF9300>(1/3/03 11:33:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/findiachinaboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What India should be</span><hr size=1> No alliances for or against.<br>
